The paper deals with decision-making in multiagent systems, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on modeling the presence and actions of other agents in an open environment suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of multiagent systems (cs.MA). The use of Monte Carlo tree search and simulations of wildfire suppression problems suggest that the paper may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO). Theoretical analyses of worst-case bounds and regret bounds suggest that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
